  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "The night before, Coco filled a bottle with water and packed two cookies, just in case the wait took a long time.",
      "zh": "前一天晚上，Coco 裝了一瓶水，還帶了兩片餅乾，以防要等很久。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice sent her a message before bed: \"Wear a warm jacket. It might be cold.\"",
      "zh": "睡前 Bernice 傳了訊息給她：「穿件保暖的外套，可能會有點冷。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco could barely sleep, and woke up before her alarm went off.",
      "zh": "Coco 幾乎睡不著，鬧鐘還沒響她就醒了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She got dressed quickly in the dark and rode her bicycle through the quiet, dry morning air.",
      "zh": "她在黑暗中快速換好衣服，騎腳踏車穿過安靜乾燥的清晨空氣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice's plan was simple: if someone touched the clock every night or every morning, they just had to be there when it happened.",
      "zh": "Bernice 的計畫很簡單：如果有人每天晚上或早上都會動那個鐘，他們只要在那個時候到場就行了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"We come before the gate opens,\" she said. \"Before anyone else is here.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「我們要在校門開之前就到，趕在其他人之前。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco was not sure this was a good idea. \"That means getting up in the dark,\" she said.",
      "zh": "Coco 不太確定這是個好主意：「那表示我們要摸黑起床。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Real cases don't happen at a convenient time,\" Bernice said, and that was the end of the argument.",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「真正的案子才不會挑方便的時間發生。」這句話讓 Coco 沒話說了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The next morning, both of them arrived while the sky was still gray and the street was almost empty.",
      "zh": "隔天早上，兩個人到的時候，天空還是灰灰的，街上幾乎沒有人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "They stood near the wall, close enough to see the clock but far enough not to be noticed.",
      "zh": "他們站在牆邊，近到能看清楚那個鐘，又遠到不容易被發現。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For almost twenty minutes, nothing happened. Coco started to think the whole plan was a waste of time.",
      "zh": "將近二十分鐘，什麼事都沒發生，Coco 開始覺得這整個計畫是在浪費時間。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Then, at exactly seven twenty, a figure walked slowly toward the gate.",
      "zh": "接著，剛好七點二十分，一個人影慢慢走向大門。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The person carried a small bag and moved like someone who had done this many times before.",
      "zh": "那個人拿著一個小袋子，動作看起來像是已經做過很多次了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice took Coco's arm without saying a word.",
      "zh": "Bernice 一句話也沒說，抓住了 Coco 的手臂。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The figure took out a small key and opened a thin door under the clock that most students never noticed.",
      "zh": "那個人拿出一把小鑰匙，打開了鐘下面一道大部分學生都沒注意過的小門。"
    },
    {
      "en": "From where they stood, they could hear a quiet click, like something being turned.",
      "zh": "從他們站的地方，可以聽到一聲輕輕的喀答聲，像是有什麼東西被轉動了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco moved forward without thinking, and her shoe hit a small stone.",
      "zh": "Coco 不小心往前移動，鞋子踢到了一顆小石頭。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The sound was small, but the figure turned around fast.",
      "zh": "聲音很小，但那個人很快就轉過頭來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For one second, Coco and the stranger looked straight at each other.",
      "zh": "有那麼一秒鐘，Coco 和那個陌生人直直看著彼此。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Then the person closed the little door, picked up the bag, and walked away fast, without a single word.",
      "zh": "接著那個人關上小門，拿起袋子，一句話也沒說，快步走開了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice ran to the clock, but the street was already empty.",
      "zh": "Bernice 跑向那個鐘，但街上已經空無一人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On the ground, half hidden under a leaf, was something the person had dropped: an old key, much older than any key at their school.",
      "zh": "地上，半藏在一片葉子底下，有一樣那個人掉下來的東西：一把舊鑰匙，看起來比學校裡任何一把鑰匙都還要舊。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco picked it up carefully and turned it over in her hand.",
      "zh": "Coco 小心翼翼地把它撿起來，在手裡翻來翻去看。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"This key is older than us,\" she said. \"Whoever this is, they've been doing this for a very long time.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「這把鑰匙比我們的年紀還大，不管是誰，他做這件事已經很久了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice looked at the small door under the clock, still slightly open. \"Then it's not a joke,\" she said quietly. \"It's a habit.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 看著那扇還微微開著的小門說：「那這就不是惡作劇，」她小聲說：「是一個習慣。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "They decided not to tell anyone yet, not even Mr. Pan, until they understood what the key really opened.",
      "zh": "他們決定先不告訴任何人，連潘老師都先不說，直到弄清楚這把鑰匙到底開的是什麼。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Before leaving, Coco checked a short list on her phone: jacket, bottle of water, notebook, and her house key.",
      "zh": "出門前，Coco 在手機上檢查一份短短的清單：外套、水瓶、筆記本，還有家裡鑰匙。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She almost forgot her cellphone charger, which would have been a real problem later that morning.",
      "zh": "她差點忘了帶手機充電器，那天早上稍晚這可能會是個大麻煩。"
    }
  ],
